message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper proposes an automatic method for quantifying coronary artery calcium (CAC) burden in low-dose chest CT scans using ConvNets for localization and regression. This involves image analysis and machine learning, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the method is in the medical domain, specifically in cardiovascular risk prediction, which suggests the relevance of medical imaging (cs.MED) and neural networks (cs.NEURON) sub-categories.
